item.description:
Customers are logical segmentations for end-users. It's a best practice to register customers in order to have their information grouped and have control on both ends. It is required to have at least one customer registered to add cards and create charges


```json
{
    "id_user": "5ed72b8fa21c26277c58411b",
    // SyncID, The ID of the user assignated by SrPago ( you should store this on your system )
    "id_pymnt_customer": "5ed66ace6b7d274f245b7685",
    // SyncID, The ID of the customer assignated by SrPago ( you should store this on your system )
    "id_pymnt_provider": "38dc9e9308898644058b4563",
    // SyncID, The ID of the payment provider assignated by SrPago
    "id_external": "869d56f0-555e-4c8c-847a-2e1ef53f6ef6",
    // String, The external id for this customer ( this identifies the customer on your system )
    "name": "Pedro Perez",
    // String, The customer full name
    "customer_key": "cus_dev_5ed66acf6758d",
    // String, The customer key
    "is_active": true,
    // Boolean, status of the customer
    "dt_create": 1591110350,
    // Integer; a Unix timestamp of the time when the user was created
    "dt_modify": null
    // Integer; a Unix timestamp of the time when the user was modified
}
```

